          </div>
          <h2
            class="mt-3 text-white"
            style="font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem); font-weight: 600; line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.28px;"
          >
            Videos Are Just HTML Files
          </h2>

          <p
            class="mt-8 max-w-2xl text-white"
            style="font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif; font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.4;"
          >
            Nous Research's Hermes Agent now has an official HyperFrames skill from HeyGen. Because
            video output is HTML, any agent that already understands HTML can write, edit, and
            render video the same way it writes web pages.
          </p>

          <div class="mt-4">
            <code
              class="rounded-md px-3 py-1.5 text-sm"
              style="font-family: ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, 'Courier New', monospace; font-weight: 400; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08); color: #2997ff;"
            >
              hermes skills install hyperframes
            </code>
